Senior Advocate of Nigeria, Femi Falana, is billed to deliver a lecture to commemorate the third anniversary in office of Ondo State governor, Rotimi Akeredolu. Wale Akinterinwa, Chairman of the Anniversary Planning Committee, made the disclosure to journalists at a briefing in Akure, the state capital. According to him, the lecture would also feature a book presentation to be chaired by Kebbi State governor, Abubakar Bagudu. He noted that the 11-day event and celebration would feature the inauguration of projects by President Muhammadu Buhari.